HEADWORD: Abarticulation
<hw>Ab`ar*tic`u*la"tion</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧b`⟦aum⟧r*t⟦icr⟧k`⟦usl⟧*l⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>ab</ets> + E. <ets>articulation</ets> : cf. F.
<ets>abarticulation</ets>. See <er>Article</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Articulation, usually that kind of articulation
which admits of free motion in the joint; diarthrosis.</def>
<rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
